<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-24T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="309" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/906: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Prendergast</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-24T14:00:00-04:00">April 24,
                                    1939—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>16. In a lengthy official manifesto just published in afternoon press
                            President Busch announces his assumption of complete power in the State
                            and promises a government of “energy and discipline.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Prendergast</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>